    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once done, transfer them to a small bowl, reserving the pan</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong> and <strong>sliced garlic</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a<strong> </strong>crack of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until the garlic has softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with your <strong>soft cheese</strong> in 180ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[280ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced courgette</strong> to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>for 7-8 min or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain and return to the pot</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will finish cooking in the sauce later!</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the courgette has started to brown, add the <strong>creamy stock</strong>, <strong>spinach </strong>and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook, covered, for 3-4 min further or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has begun to thicken</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked tortiglioni </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for a final 1-2 min or until the Tenderstem is cooked with a slight bite \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy white bean & double green wholewheat tortiglioni</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-white-bean-and-double-green-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy white bean & double green wholewheat tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and season with a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>toasted pumpkin seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
